{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5e9b5393-6538-4baf-8fea-45b2337496f4","content":"The template.json looks mostly well-structured but has a couple of issues before publishing:\n\n**Missing required field:**\n- `$schema` — recommended for validation (e.g., `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`)\n\n**Missing recommended fields:**\n- `preferNameDirectory` — helps `dotnet new` create a subfolder\n- `description` — important for NuGet discoverability; without it the template listing will be blank\n\n**Potential concern:**\n- `\"defaultValue\": \"net9.0\"` — .NET 9 is current, but consider whether your template source actually builds against both TFMs correctly\n\n**Looks good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `sourceName`, `author`, `classifications`, `tags`, and `symbols` are all valid and properly formatted\n\n**Verdict:** Not quite ready. At minimum, add a `description` field — NuGet templates without one appear incomplete in `dotnet new search` results. Adding `$schema` is also strongly recommended for tooling support.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2efd9cfd-3819-4760-9564-375966414463","outputTokens":242,"requestId":"5017:12E269:13B27E5:161E993:6A06709D"},"id":"5c9b02cc-a6a1-440e-9449-e529f480714b","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:02:29.849Z","parentId":"e555cb0e-80e3-4086-8e8f-a9a2bd840632"}
